=== Purpose ===
To link to articles in [[Wikisource]] editions of the [[New International Encyclopedia]].

=== Usage ===
<code><nowiki>{{NIE poster}}</nowiki></code>

or

<code><nowiki>{{NIE poster|Article Name}}</nowiki></code>

or

<code><nowiki>{{NIE poster|Article Name|Display Name}}</nowiki></code>

In addition, there is a <tt>year</tt> parameter which defaults to 1905.

=== Examples ===
{{NIE poster|Bœhmeria}}
{{NIE poster|Bœhmeria|Boehmeria}}
<code><nowiki>{{NIE poster|Bœhmeria}}</nowiki></code>

This result is displayed in the top box to the right.  If the NIE article name looks too ugly, use:

<code><nowiki>{{NIE poster|Bœhmeria|Boehmeria}}</nowiki></code>

This result is displayed in the bottom box to the right.  If no article name is specified, the PAGENAME is used.

=== Usage tips ===
When you put this template on a Wikipedia article, please be kind to the regular Wikipedians who are working on those articles. This should be placed at the bottom of the article, usually the External links section. Sometimes it simply won't fit within the Wikipedia article at the bottom, so you may have to use some judgement:  think about using the in-line version, {{tl|Cite NIE}}.  If the article is about a Wikisource author, it will usually be better to just put a link in the "Works about" section of the author page in Wikisource using [[Wikisource:Template:NIE Link]].

